This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it proposes a system for human gait and walking direction recognition in Wi-Fi networks. The paper also involves the use of Channel State Information (CSI) measurements from different receivers, which is a common technique used in wireless networking research. 

The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically an attention-based Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) encoder-decoder framework, which suggests that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the paper involves image processing techniques for capturing human walking dynamics, which suggests that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Finally, the paper involves experimental results and evaluation, which suggests that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SD (Sound).
